The newly opened Dei Gratia campus, situated at 8 Acacia Crescent in West Acres, held both its opening and graduation ceremony on Saturday March 12. Proud patents, family and friends gathered at the premises, dressed to the nines for the much-awaited graduation of their loved ones. Dei Gratia offers a wide variety of courses, from beauty, business practice, hairdressing and early childhood development, to basic firefighting, risk assessment and working with mining machinery.March 12â€™s graduation saw 15 students graduate in their hairdressing trade test and 64 graduates in hairdressing skills. A further three people graduated with hairdressing level two, another one in hairdressing level three and three for hairdressing level four. There were 11 graduates for the working with heights course. Attendees of the graduation were treated to a stunning showcase of talent by the Ramps to Runway models and Rhythm Image dancers. ALSO READ: Golfers in fine form for 2022 Club Championships at Malelane Golf Club Dei Gratia held a raffle for some lucky prize-winners in the audience, and some graduates also received small gifts from the campus for their hard work. The school also offered a discount on course fees for the first 10 people to sign up to the campus on that day. Dei Gratia welcomes anyone willing to either further their education in certain areas or learn new skills, to visit the new campus and learn more about what the school has to offer. ALSO READ: Airlink Pumas ruthless in defeating DHL Western Province in Cape Town